{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CSJkCeUWzGsGC93BSXvDYf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The oracle exits 0 — the case passes.\n\n**What was wrong and what was fixed:**\n\n1. **Root cause:** The `expired-tls-secret` in the `demo` namespace held a TLS certificate valid only from 2020-01-01 to 2020-01-02 (expired ~5 years ago), causing all HTTPS connections to fail with certificate validation errors.\n\n2. **Secondary issue:** `/tmp/ingress_env` had `INGRESS_NODE_IP=` (empty) because the precondition script didn't capture the node IP correctly. Fixed by writing `172.18.0.4` (the kind node's internal IP) into the file.\n\n3. **Fix:** Generated a new 2048-bit RSA key and leaf certificate signed by the existing `Test CA` (from `/tmp/test-ca.crt` / `/tmp/test-ca.key`), valid 2025–2027, matching the original SAN (`demo.example.com`). Updated the secret in-place with `kubectl apply`. Nginx picked up the new cert within a few seconds and HTTPS now returns `hello` with exit code 0."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":153,"cache_read_input_tokens":43713,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":153},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b8b9210b-61ee-4e04-948d-a3891486dd5c","uuid":"a9ebecf0-d866-41b7-a82e-4b40ef395e98","request_id":"req_011Cc4AecRXA181ra9LaWgYL"}
